{
  "text": "Contrast-enhanced ultrasound (CEUS), with lipid-or protein-stabilized gas microbubbles, plays an important role in patient care and is evolving as a fundamental screening tool in cardiology, oncology and gynecology [CITATION_1] . CEUS is used in a variety of clinical applications such as detecting and characterizing focal liver lesions [CITATION_2] , evaluating cerebral circulation for stroke [CITATION_3] ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "207611907",
